article.headline: Savannah St. 61, Utah Valley St. 46
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. (AP) -- Curtis Brown hit two 3-pointers and Lazarius Coleman added a trio of layups in a 26-5 second-half run that carried Savannah State to a 61-46 victory over Utah Valley on Saturday. Chris Linton broke a 29-29 deadlock on a layup with 18:19 to play and Jovonni Shuler ended the run on a layup, making it 56-34 with 5:52 remaining. Raye Bailey led the Tigers (12-17) with 13 points and Coleman and Joseph Flegler each added 12. Coleman also had 11 rebounds. Ryan Toolson had 18 points for Utah Valley (12-14) and Richard Troyer and Jordan Brady added 10 apiece. Bjorn Bohley's layup with a second left in the first half gave the Tigers a 26-25 lead at the intermission.
